{"type":"message","id":"e8c31f7b","parentId":"46875070","timestamp":"2026-04-19T18:15:59.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error says `mode=\"session\" requires thread=true`. I need to use `mode=\"run\"` for non-thread-bound sessions, or add `thread=true` for thread-bound sessions. Since this is a Telegram group chat (not a thread context), I'll use `mode=\"run\"` for one-shot sessions, but the user wanted persistent sessions. Let me use `mode=\"run\"` with longer timeouts for now, as thread=true would require Discord thread IDs.\n\nActually, looking at the docs: \"For Discord, default ACP harness requests to thread-bound persistent sessions (thread: true, mode: \"session\")\". This is Telegram, not Discord. For Telegram, `mode=\"run\"` is probably better for isolated sessions.\n\n\nSo I'll spawn all agents with `mode=\"run\"` to create fresh isolated sessions that each return results when they complete.","thinkingSignature":"54c65213d22bbcc0459dfbb12a7e89ae6d3df3f400d3c34c14e14ce91f7ca75c"},{"type":"text","text":"`mode=\"session\"` cần `thread=true` (chỉ Discord thread). Spawn lại với `mode=\"run\"` cho Telegram:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ewaury86ved7_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are a senior frontend developer agent. Your workspace: /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-fe/ (create if not exists). You are part of the AHV DTLX Ecosystem project. Read your workspace SOUL.md/AGENTS.md if present. When done, respond briefly with your agent name and status \"READY\".","label":"dtlx:senior-frontend","runtime":"subagent","runTimeoutSeconds":120,"mode":"run","cleanup":"keep"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ewaury86ved7_2","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are a senior backend developer agent. Your workspace: /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-dtlx-be/ (create if not exists). You are part of the AHV DTLX Ecosystem project. Read