{"type":"message","id":"bec16275","parentId":"c985101b","timestamp":"2026-04-20T01:50:01.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Backend is listening on `*:5555` (all interfaces) and curl to the public IP works fine. But ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED from the browser could be:1. The browser was loaded before the backend started2. Browser cached the old URL3. Firewall blocking port 55554. Vite dev server proxy issue\n\nWait, actually - the issue might be that the frontend is at `http://103.253.21.139:3002` and the backend is at `http://103.253.21.139:5555`. The browser can access both via network. But maybe the backend is actually not accessible externally and Vite is supposed to proxy it.\n\n\nThe backend is actually running on port 5555 and listening on all interfaces, so the public IP should work. The real issue is that browsers can't reach the server when Vite is running on the same machine through Docker or a VPN, since port 5555 isn't exposed in those environments.\n\nI should check if the port is blocked by a firewall, or better yet, set up a Vite proxy in the dev server configuration to route `/api` requests to the backend instead of having the frontend hit it directly. I need to check the actual backend code to see how it's binding to the port and whether it's configured to listen on all interfaces rather than just localhost.","thinkingSignature":"a6311091cb8a07e79fa902aebe10d2894fdb2e45ea0733b6adab43d325102eb8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yrtg2q3s65ef_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/server.ts | grep -A5 \"listen\\|host\\|0\\.0\\.0\\.0\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":338,"cacheRead":157500,"cacheWrite":289,"totalTokens":158237,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776649790646,"responseId":"0634b940876419489c86794da067703e"}}
