{"type":"message","id":"fbad9f5f","parentId":"036231e7","timestamp":"2026-04-20T01:50:09.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backend listens on `port` which from `.env` is 5555. Since it doesn't specify a host, it defaults to listening on all interfaces. But it could be binding to localhost only.\n\nActually, looking at the `ss` output: `*:5555 *:*` — the `*` means all interfaces. So it should be accessible.\n\nBut wait - the backend is running inside a background process. Let me check if it's still running and accessible.\n\nActually the backend IS running (curl returned OK). So the issue is something else.\n\nWait, maybe the issue is the OLD background process. Let me check what's running:","thinkingSignature":"26fc5e09a0806027aa4126c5b9b9ab7936d9f790cd4729a7a9769f53a6da18ff"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tg5515ic1429_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep \"node\\|server\" | grep -v grep | grep -v openclaw"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":127,"output":174,"cacheRead":157646,"cacheWrite":529,"totalTokens":158476,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776649802094,"responseId":"0634b94b5ebbdb23bfba1ccec29db972"}}
