{"type":"message","id":"defb6a54","parentId":"5f0ba000","timestamp":"2026-04-20T01:53:00.028Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear - the backend CORS is set to `origin: '*'` but the frontend is sending credentials (cookies). The fix is either:\n\n1. Change backend CORS to allow specific origins instead of wildcard\n2. Or change frontend to not send credentials\n3. Or use Vite proxy completely (which we already set up)\n\nThe best fix is to update the axios config to use `withCredentials: false` OR update the backend CORS. Since the frontend proxy is working, the simplest fix is to ensure all API calls go through the proxy (http://localhost:3002/api/...) instead of direct to the backend.\n\nLet me check the axios config to see if `withCredentials` is set.","thinkingSignature":"9119ad1faf5f309d817dff040adbd29123af7a37f60dc049c15f13378be896df"},{"type":"text","text":"Vấn đề: backend CORS `origin: '*'` không hoạt động với `credentials`. Sửa nhanh:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jkxzb2x5oepx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && grep -n \"withCredentials\\|credentials\\|origin\" src/app.ts | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":245,"cacheRead":165577,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":165822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776649968326,"responseId":"0634b9f2a28d36fc6ab6398c9c23d08c"}}
