{"type":"message","id":"c987d834","parentId":"86810394","timestamp":"2026-04-20T01:53:08.108Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is `origin: '*'` with `credentials: true`. The fix is to either:\n1. Change origin to specific domain\n2. Change credentials to false\n\nSince the Vite proxy is already working, the simplest approach is to just make sure the frontend uses the proxy. But since the frontend is still calling the backend directly (using `http://103.253.21.139:5555`), let me fix the CORS to allow the specific domain OR disable credentials.\n\nThe best fix is to change `credentials: true` to `credentials: false` for now. Or better, change `origin: '*'` to `origin: ['http://103.253.21.139:3002']`.\n\n\nI'll go with updating the CORS configuration to accept the frontend's domain directly.","thinkingSignature":"03748ec140f3badafcb360ad48da3afdff4b528ed025573abd6d6f29f347c82d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mf0c4d7ohb7f_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend/src/app.ts","offset":15,"limit":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":135,"output":232,"cacheRead":165199,"cacheWrite":561,"totalTokens":166127,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776649980103,"responseId":"0634b9fd744e0d798c16bae921dd3206"}}
