{"type":"message","id":"50564f89","parentId":"c3a582ea","timestamp":"2026-04-20T02:08:38.902Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The axios interceptor uses `import.meta.env.VITE_API_SERVER`. But in the .env, I have `VITE_API_SERVER=http://localhost:5555`. The issue is that the frontend is calling `localhost:5555` directly instead of going through the proxy.\n\nThere are two options:\n1. Change all API files to use relative URLs (e.g., `/api/v1/...`) and rely on the Vite proxy\n2. Set VITE_API_SERVER to the actual backend URL accessible from the user's browser\n\nThe problem is the user's browser accesses the frontend at `http://103.253.21.139:3002`, but the axios calls `localhost:5555` which doesn't exist on the user's machine.\n\n\nI think the best approach is to switch the frontend to relative URLs and let the Vite dev server proxy handle the routing, since the backend is already configured to accept requests from `http://103.253.21.139:3002`. I need to set `VITE_API_SERVER` to an empty string or relative path so axios uses `/api/v1/...` instead of the full absolute URL.","thinkingSignature":"4cf489fc837e7d110c2927ff80ecb75ca9f3f8bdebfac756dcf27a05713c27a4"},{"type":"text","text":"Vấn đề: axios dùng absolute URL `localhost:5555` — browser của user không truy cập được `localhost`. Đổi sang proxy relative:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_92lb6u5quxvy_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend/.env","content":"VITE_PORT=3002\nVITE_API_SERVER=\nVITE_API_TIMEOUT=10000\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":196,"output":349,"cacheRead":168080,"cacheWrite":324,"totalTokens":168949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776650908568,"responseId":"0634bd9e06f7483a8987caaaa885a7a1"}}
