{"type":"message","id":"e36a7248","parentId":"e78341db","timestamp":"2026-04-20T02:09:44.675Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error shows `http://localhost:5000` - not 5555! And the issue is \"The request client is not a secure context and the resource is in more-private address space loopback\" - this is the new Chrome 129+ privacy policy where `localhost` is treated as a more-private address space.\n\nThe frontend is still using `localhost:5000` somewhere. Looking at the error, it's `auth.api.js:6`. The browser has cached the old Vite bundle with `localhost:5000`.\n\nLet me check all the API files to find where `localhost:5000` is hardcoded, and also clear the Vite cache.","thinkingSignature":"b8b7ce7cb3fe10ff1587d18a21ec5e639d2a32be5372f2f34ea26162da851c13"},{"type":"text","text":"Frontend đang dùng `localhost:5000` (cached bundle cũ). Xóa Vite cache + tìm hardcoded:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gvs1jnvqxx3s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-frontend && grep -rn \"localhost:5000\\|localhost:5555\" src/ --include=\"*.js\" --include=\"*.jsx\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":2477,"output":249,"cacheRead":169410,"cacheWrite":22,"totalTokens":172158,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776650972257,"responseId":"0634bdde5078e22975f3b20de33492b1"}}
