{"type":"message","id":"c3c465d7","parentId":"339e8b2e","timestamp":"2026-04-20T02:12:06.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Backend is still running on port 5555. And curl through the proxy works. So the 404 in the browser might be because:\n1. The browser's request doesn't match the proxy config - maybe the browser is sending a preflight OPTIONS request that the backend doesn't handle\n2. The auth endpoint specifically\n\nLet me test the proxy with curl more carefully - making sure it's the same as what the browser does.\n\nActually wait - curl was returning the backend response. But now the browser gets 404. Let me check if there's a CORS preflight issue - maybe the `withCredentials: true` causes a preflight OPTIONS request that needs to be handled.\n\n\nThe OPTIONS request is probably hitting the backend without the proper CORS headers configured for preflight, since the backend only whitelists GET and HEAD in the Access-Control-Allow-Methods list. Let me trace through the actual proxy logs to see what's happening.","thinkingSignature":"723966d1a0348fdeb757570a0dd45121de334f8cad021406b4535fd10bdb4988"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1pe8v5hcvgw2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -H \"Origin: http://103.253.21.139:3002\" http://localhost:3002/api/v1/auth/signin -d '{\"username\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"admin123\"}' 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":110,"output":277,"cacheRead":173366,"cacheWrite":1074,"totalTokens":174827,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776651116544,"responseId":"0634be6e40b4093ff734d3fecbbd2d8a"}}
