{"type":"message","id":"cb73080a","parentId":"ceb2f83a","timestamp":"2026-04-20T02:12:15.479Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The curl test with the Origin header works and returns the auth error. So the proxy is working fine. But the browser is getting 404. \n\nThis means the frontend bundle is still cached or using an old version. The browser might be loading a cached JS file that still has the old `localhost:5000` URL.\n\nActually wait - looking at the browser error message: `POST http://103.253.21.139:3002/api/v1/auth/signin 404`. The URL IS correct (`103.253.21.139:3002/api/v1/auth/signin`) but it's getting 404. \n\nLet me check: is the Vite dev server still running? And is the proxy working?","thinkingSignature":"e6113412aaca3f03bb892a2a169bd79b0ff1112d0dd249c4c47e359645852b50"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rql7hmcb24ji_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ss -tlnp | grep 3002 && curl -sv http://localhost:3002/api/v1/auth/signin -X POST -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"username\":\"admin\",\"password\":\"admin123\"}' 2>&1 | grep -E \"< HTTP|200|404|OK|fail\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":215,"output":241,"cacheRead":174087,"cacheWrite":678,"totalTokens":175221,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776651126442,"responseId":"0634be7705b1c249d55f586ff7cf9e32"}}
