{"type":"message","id":"2487ffd3","parentId":"dce6d61d","timestamp":"2026-04-20T02:12:26.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The proxy IS working - it's forwarding to the backend and getting the auth error response. But the HTTP status is 404 (because the auth service returns 404 for wrong password). So the backend returns HTTP 404, and the frontend axios code treats all non-2xx as errors.\n\nSo actually, the proxy IS working! The issue is that:\n1. The URL is correct: `http://103.253.21.139:3002/api/v1/auth/signin` ✅\n2. The CORS is fixed ✅\n3. The auth endpoint is responding (wrong password → 404) ✅\n\n\n4. The problem is just the wrong password, not the setup itself.\n\nThe user probably hasn't actually tested logging in with the correct credentials yet - they're seeing the 404 error and thinking something's broken with the connection, but really they just need to enter the right password.","thinkingSignature":"bc13470ff30722bf735811d387811a42df699ecfd9955a5efe201924e12d5a53"},{"type":"text","text":"Proxy đang hoạt động tốt! Backend trả về **HTTP 404** — đây là response bình thường khi **sai mật khẩu**, không phải lỗi CORS hay proxy.\n\nCó nghĩa là:\n- ✅ API URL đúng: `http://103.253.21.139:3002/api/v1/auth/signin`\n- ✅ CORS đã fix\n- ✅ Proxy hoạt động\n- ✅ Backend nhận request\n\n**Vấn đề chỉ là: sai mật khẩu.**\n\nBạn dùng credentials nào để login? Hoặc cho tôi biết tài khoản admin mặc định của hệ thống — tôi sẽ check trong MongoDB."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":271,"output":382,"cacheRead":174483,"cacheWrite":676,"totalTokens":175812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776651135751,"responseId":"0634be8176123fb1f0b1f3c5ea0797c3"}}
